  "title": "Electrical Technician #78927",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Fire Protection Services</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Electrical Technician</strong></li><li>Working Location: Sims Ave (7mins walk from Aljunied MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 6 days (Mon – Sat, 8AM – 7PM (with OT))</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Gross $1,000 - $1,800 + VB</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Carry out electrical installation, termination, and testing of equipment and systems on-site.</li><li>Assist in M&E coordination to align electrical works with other services (e.g., HVAC, plumbing).</li><li>Support commissioning activities, including PA addressable systems (if applicable).</li><li>Troubleshoot and repair electrical faults and system issues promptly.</li><li>Interpret M&E and FP drawings, schematic diagrams, and construction plans.</li><li>Conduct routine inspections and preventive maintenance.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) standards and Energy Market Authority (EMA) regulations.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of work progress, tools, and materials used.</li><li>Communicate effectively with the site team, subcontractors, and main contractors.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 1 year of hands-on experience as an Electrical Technician in construction or M&E projects.</li><li>Proficient in electrical wiring, cabling, panel termination, and containment installation.</li><li>Familiarity with PA addressable systems is an advantage.</li><li>Knowledge of SS 638, BCA site safety requirements, and EMA guidelines.</li><li>Able to work independently and as part of a site-based team.</li><li>Experience in ELV systems (e.g., fire alarm, CCTV, access control).</li><li>Able to read and interpret M&E layout drawings and single-line diagrams.</li><li>Valid CoreTrade certification is an advantage.</li><li>Work-at-Height (WAH) and hot work/electrical safety certifications preferred.</li><li>Familiarity with SCDF submission standards and authorities’ inspections is a bonus.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#78927 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
